13:["$","p",null,{"children":["The NMN architecture is not just a technical innovation, but a reflection of the shifting landscape of the AI industry. As ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://www.forbes.com/sites/forbestechcouncil/2022/02/22/the-future-of-ai-in-business/?sh=66a94f6d66f2","children":"Forbes notes"}],", companies are no longer just investing in AI research, but are actively deploying these technologies in real-world applications. The ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://www.marketsandmarkets.com/Market-Reports/ai-in-industry-market-261697444.html","children":"market"}]," is expected to grow significantly in the coming years, with ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://www.idc.com/getdoc.jsp?containerId=PR857342021","children":"IDC predicting"}]," that the global AI market will reach $190 billion by 2025.\nThe ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://github.com/topics/machine-learning","children":"developer signal"}]," is clear: NMNs are not just a novelty, but a significant development in the field of machine learning. As ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://www.kdnuggets.com/2022/02/neural-matter-networks.html","children":"KDNuggets notes"}],", the community is responding positively to NMNs, with many ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://github.com/search?q=neural+matter+networks","children":"open-source implementations"}]," already available. However, it's essential to approach these developments with a critical eye and consider the ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Reality_gap","children":"reality gap"}]," between demo and deployment.\nThe ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://www.cbinsights.com/research/machine-learning-trends/","children":"industry map"}]," is shifting, with companies like ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://ai.google/","children":"Google"}]," and ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/blog/tag/machine-learning/","children":"Microsoft"}]," investing heavily in AI research and development. The ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://www.forbes.com/sites/forbestechcouncil/2022/02/22/the-future-of-ai-in-business/?sh=66a94f6d66f2","children":"competitive advantage"}]," will go to those who can effectively deploy these technologies in real-world applications. As ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://www.theverge.com/2022/2/15/22931440/ai-research-uncertainty-principle","children":"The Verge notes"}],", the line between demo and deployment is often blurred, and actual performance may vary significantly.\nIn conclusion, the introduction of NMNs marks a significant development in the field of machine learning. While the hype surrounding these networks is undeniable, it's crucial to separate what's genuinely new from what's repackaged marketing. The real story here is not just about the technology itself, but about the potential impact on the industry and the community. As ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://www.wired.com/story/the-future-of-ai-is-not-what-you-think/","children":"Wired notes"}],", the future of AI is not just about the tech, but about the people and the companies behind it."]}]
